main event: A radar object was tracked over Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, on an unspecified date.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar at an altitude of 9,600 feet and was estimated to be 30 to 50 feet in diameter., The duration of the sighting was approximately 3 minutes., Initial impressions were to discount the incident as a natural phenomenon., The Air Force later identified the object as likely being a commercial airliner., No other unusual activity or sightings were reported in the area at the time.
